<span id="freeTextContainer8631619108374359202">Delany&apos;s prose takes some getting used to and I have even read reviews of his work that sang to the tune of, &quot;Does he have to be so high and mighty in his verbiage?&quot;<br/><br/>The answer is, yes! He does. <i>Someone</i> has to. <br/><br/>Get off your lackadaisical bum, you shoddy reader you, and expect something more from yourself and the writer. Stop kowtowing to the school of thought that indicates, &quot;a simple word instead of an esoteric one.&quot; What the hell are all the rest of the words in the dictionary for? Why have com</span>
  <span id="freeText8631619108374359202" style="display:none">Delany's prose takes some getting used to and I have even read reviews of his work that sang to the tune of, "Does he have to be so high and mighty in his verbiage?"<br /><br />The answer is, yes! He does. <i>Someone</i> has to. <br /><br />Get off your lackadaisical bum, you shoddy reader you, and expect something more from yourself and the writer. Stop kowtowing to the school of thought that indicates, "a simple word instead of an esoteric one." What the hell are all the rest of the words in the dictionary for? Why have complex syntaxes and tenses and grammatical moods if we restrain ourselves to pedestrian fair?<br /><br />Looking for an easy Sunday afternoon read? Look elsewhere. <br />Looking to make some new neuron connections in your brain? The destination is before you. </span>
