<span id="freeTextContainer2516561791726384756">2 stars is a VERY generous rating for this book. No point, no focus, and a world that we&apos;re expected to already understand even though it&apos;s only ever &quot;explained&quot; through the characters&apos; interactions with it. It&apos;s great that Delany &quot;predicted the internet&quot; in this book, but to try to parse that out of the obtuse writing was a chore, and certainly not a pleasure that I expect to get out of reading.<br/><br/>1.5 stars at best.</span>
  <span id="freeText2516561791726384756" style="display:none">2 stars is a VERY generous rating for this book. No point, no focus, and a world that we're expected to already understand even though it's only ever "explained" through the characters' interactions with it. It's great that Delany "predicted the internet" in this book, but to try to parse that out of the obtuse writing was a chore, and certainly not a pleasure that I expect to get out of reading.<br /><br />1.5 stars at best.</span>
